Booleanator
===========

Adds #to_boolean method to Integer, NilClass and String, for massaging Rails
param strings in the model, since Rails only does this in the controller context.

Example
=======

  options[:allow_comments] = '0'
  options[:allow_comments].to_boolean # => false

Check out more at github.

